Living in Fukuoka, Japan has been an incredible experience for me. From the delicious food to the friendly people, there is always something new to discover and enjoy in this vibrant city.

One of the first things I noticed about Fukuoka was its food culture. There are so many amazing restaurants and food stalls throughout the city, each offering unique and delicious dishes. I quickly became a fan of tonkotsu ramen, which is a specialty of the city. The rich and savory broth combined with the tender noodles and succulent pork is an absolute delight for the taste buds.

Another thing I love about Fukuoka is its natural beauty. The city is surrounded by lush green hills and scenic beaches. One of my favorite spots is Ohori Park, which is a beautiful park with a large lake in the center. It's a perfect place to relax and enjoy the peaceful surroundings.

Fukuoka is also known for its friendly and welcoming people. From shopkeepers to coworkers, everyone has been incredibly kind and helpful to me during my time here. I feel grateful to have had the opportunity to interact with so many amazing people who have made me feel at home in this city.

One of the biggest challenges of living in Fukuoka for me was the language barrier. Japanese can be a difficult language to learn, and it was challenging at first to communicate with locals. However, I found that people were always patient and willing to help me learn, which made the experience much easier.

Overall, living in Fukuoka has been an unforgettable experience. From the food to the nature to the people, there is so much to love about this city. I feel grateful to have had the opportunity to live and work here and would highly recommend it to anyone who is considering it.





